<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id775c3826-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s410mm–3"><num value="410mm–3">§ 410mm–3.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id775c3827-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s410mm–3/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content> Not more than $800,000 are authorized to be appropriated for development of the park.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id775c3828-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s410mm–3/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content> Not more than $200,000 are authorized to be appropriated for acquisition of lands and interests in land within the park.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id775c3829-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/99/565/s5">Pub. L. 99–565, § 5</ref>, <date date="1986-10-27">Oct. 27, 1986</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/100/3183">100 Stat. 3183</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
